OL,3,CMenu calorie labelling fails to
OL,4,Cencourage healthier options
OL,6,FBut a new study, led by researchers
OL,7,Ffrom the University of Liverpool,
OL,8,Ffound that while the policy has
OL,9,Fincreased customer awareness of
OL,10,Fcalories in food, it has not had a
OL,11,Fsubstantial effect on consumption.
OL,13,FThe study used customer surveys taken
OL,14,Fin 330 food outlets across England,
OL,15,Fcovering cafes, fast food restaurants,
OL,16,Fpubs and sit-down restaurants, both
OL,17,Fbefore and after mandatory calorie
OL,18,Flabelling was introduced.
