OL,3,CMenu calorie labelling fails to
OL,4,Cencourage healthier options
OL,6,FThis was despite the proportion of
OL,7,Fcustomers noticing information about
OL,8,Fthe calories in their meals rising
OL,9,Ffrom 16.5% before the policy was
OL,10,Fintroduced to 31.8% afterwards.
OL,12,FJust 22% of customers reported using
OL,13,Fcalorie information when making their
OL,14,Ffood choices after labelling was
OL,15,Fintroduced, with awareness and use of
OL,16,Fthe information higher among women,
OL,17,Folder adults and people in higher
OL,18,Fsocioeconomic groups.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
